Ambulance Service (Fees) Amendment Regulations 2014

I, the Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, make the following regulations under the Ambulance Service Act 1982 .

16 December 2014

C. WARNER

Governor

By Her Excellency's Command,

MICHAEL DARREL JOSEPH FERGUSON

Minister for Health

1. Short title
    These regulations may be cited as the Ambulance Service (Fees) Amendment Regulations 2014 .

2. Commencement
    These regulations take effect on the twenty-eighth day after the day on which their making is notified in the Gazette.

3. Principal Regulations
    In these regulations, the Ambulance Service (Fees) Regulations 2011 are referred to as the Principal Regulations.

4.
    The amendments effected by this regulation have been incorporated into the authorised version of the Ambulance Service (Fees) Regulations 2011 .

5.
    The amendment effected by this regulation has been incorporated into the authorised version of the Ambulance Service (Fees) Regulations 2011 .

6.
    The amendment effected by this regulation has been incorporated into the authorised version of the Ambulance Service (Fees) Regulations 2011 .

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 24 December 2014

These regulations are administered in the Department of Health and Human Services.
